SIMPLE: struggle
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Struggle
<hw>Strug"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Struggled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Struggling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>strogelen</ets>; cf. Icel. <ets>strj<?/ka</ets> to stroke, to beat,
to flog, Sw. <ets>stryka</ets> to stroke, to strike, Dan.
<ets>stryge</ets>, G. <ets>straucheln</ets> to stumble. Cf.
<er>Stroll</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To strive, or to make efforts,
with a twisting, or with contortions of the body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To use great efforts; to labor hard; to strive; to
contend forcibly; <as>as, to <ex>struggle</ex> to save one's life; to
<ex>struggle</ex> with the waves; to <ex>struggle</ex> with
adversity</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The brave men, living and dead, who <qex>struggled</qex> here,
have consecrated it [Gettysburg] far above our power to add or
detract.</q> <rj><qau>Lincoln.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To labor in pain or anguish; to be in agony; to
labor in any kind of difficulty or distress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is wisdom to beware,⟦br⟧
And better shun the bait than <qex>struggle</qex> in the snare.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To strive; contend; labor; endeavor.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Struggle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Struggle
<hw>Strug"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
violent effort or efforts with contortions of the body; agony;
distress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Great labor; forcible effort to obtain an object, or
to avert an evil.</def> <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Contest; contention; strife.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An honest might look upon the <qex>struggle</qex> with
indifference.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Endeavor; effort; contest; labor;
difficulty.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Struggler</ent>⟦br⟧
